1
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:13,560
The Satanic Nebula.

2
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,880
Or the Lagoon of Lost Stars.

3
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,720
Or we could go to Brighton.

4
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:22,600
I've got a whole day worked out.

5
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:26,520
Sorry, but as you can see,
I've got plans.

6
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,840
-Have you?
-Look at me.

7
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:31,320
Yeah, okay.

8
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,920
No, no, no. Like, no.

9
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:38,000
-Look at me.
-Yep. Looking.

10
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:40,360
Seriously?

11
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:42,000
Why is your face all coloured in?

12
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:46,040
7:15, meeting me, you are.

13
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,000
Date. Second one.

14
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:55,080
Got words out. Not in the right
order but hey, maths teacher.

15
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,080
BOTH: Out!

16
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,680
-Are you taller?
-Heels.

17
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:05,200
What, do you have to
reach a high shelf?

18
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:07,600
Right, gotta go. Going to be late.

19
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,280
-For a shelf?
-Bye.

20
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,200
(PHONE RINGING)

21
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,240
There you go,
you've got another playmate.

22
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:23,880
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

23
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:26,120
DOCTOR: Hardly anyone
in the universe has that number.

24
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:28,080
Well, I've got it.

25
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:30,760
Yes, from some woman in a shop.

26
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:32,280
We still don't know who that was.

27
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,000
Is that her now?

28
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,960
There are very few people
that it could be.

29
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,920
(RINGING CONTINUES)

30
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,840
-Don't.
-Why not?

31
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:45,000
Because if you answer it,
something will happen.

32
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:46,880
-What?
-A thing.

33
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,640
(SCOFFING) It's just a phone, Clara.

34
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,400
Nothing happens
when you answer the phone.

35
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,400
-(SCREAMING)
-(WORMS SCREECHING)

36
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,600
-Doctor?
-Don't touch it!

37
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,840
-Where are we? How did we get here?
-Who are you?

38
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,880
Sorry, what's going on?
I don't understand.

39
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,280
-What is that thing?
-It's a memory worm.

40
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,480
-What happened to your face?
-DOCTOR: Deletes your memories.

41
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,440
-Did you see her face?
-How did I get here?

42
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:15,400
DOCTOR: The same way
we all did. But we've all forgotten.

43
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:18,000
-And who are you?
-DOCTOR OVER INTERCOM: I am the Doctor,

44
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:20,200
a Time Lord from Gallifrey.

45
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:23,600
I've agreed to this memory wipe
of my own free will.

46
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,360
CLARA OVER INTERCOM:
I am Clara Oswald, human.

47
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,960
I've agreed to this memory wipe
of my own free will.

48
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,520
Do I really have to
touch that worm thing?

49
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,280
DOCTOR: Yes, you do.
And change your shoes. You're next, Psi.

50
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:37,360
PSI OVER INTERCOM:
I'm Psi, augmented human.

51
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:41,680
I have agreed to this memory
wipe of my own free will.

52
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,800
SAIBRA OVER INTERCOM:
I am Saibra, mutant human.

53
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:51,800
I've agreed to this memory wipe
of my own free will.

54
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,400
(BEEP)

55
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:01,200
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

56
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:36,520
ARCHITECT:
This is a recorded message.

57
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,240
ARCHITECT:
This is a recorded message.

58
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,920
I am the Architect.

59
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,560
Your last memory is
of receiving a contact

60
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:45,000
from an unknown agency. Me.

61
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:48,600
Everything since has been
erased from your minds.

62
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:52,040
Now, pay close attention
to this briefing.

63
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,480
This is the bank of Karabraxos,

64
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:57,160
the most secure bank in the galaxy.

65
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,480
A fortress for the super-rich.

66
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,760
If you can afford your own star system,

67
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,280
this is where you'd keep it.

68
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:06,040
No one sets foot on the planet
without protocols.

69
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:10,240
All movement is monitored,
all air consumption regulated.

70
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:13,760
DNA is authenticated at every stage.

71
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:18,000
-Intruders will be incinerated.
-(RAPID BEEPING)

72
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:20,760
Each vault, buried deep in the Earth,

73
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:24,120
is accessed by a drop slot
on the planet's surface.

74
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:27,760
It's atomically sealed,
an unbreakable lock.

75
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,880
The atoms have all been scrambled.

76
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,400
Your presence on this planet
ls unauthorised.

77
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,960
A team will have been dispatched
to terminate you.

78
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:39,240
-(POUNDING ON DOOR)
-GUARD: This is bank security. Open up!

79
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:43,080
ARCHITECT: Your survival depends
on following my instructions.

80
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:45,160
Open up and you shall be
humanely disposed of.

81
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,640
There's another exit.

82
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,880
ARCHITECT: All the information
you need is in this case.

83
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,360
-What are you doing?
-PSI: Downloading.

84
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,640
Augmented. Nice.

85
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:59,800
ARCHITECT: The bank of Karabraxos
is impregnable.

86
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:01,360
GUARD: Please stand away from the door!

87
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,480
We do not wish to hurt you
before incineration!

88
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,560
ARCHITECT: 7he bank of Karabraxos
has never been breached.

89
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:10,640
You will rob the bank of Karabraxos.

90
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,880
Report.

91
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:17,000
GUARD: (PANTING) Sorry.
Hello, who is this?

92
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:20,080
This is Ms Delphox,
head of bank security.

93
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:23,040
I sent you to investigate
an off-world intruder.

94
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,200
GUARD: Did you?

95
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,600
Well, I was wondering
what we're doing here.

96
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,640
-We found these amazing worms.
-(SQUEAKING)

97
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,520
-(EXHALES)
-(DOOR OPENS)

98
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:42,720
Unwelcome guests.
We're going to need the Teller.

99
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:51,560
-(LOW SNARLING)
-Are you hungry, boy?

100
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:00,680
Okay, okay, okay! Stop, stop, stop!

101
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,800
(PANTING) Far enough.

102
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,920
Augmented human.

103
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:08,240
Computer augmented, yes?
Mainframe in your head?

104
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,000
I'm a gamer.
Sorry, who put you in charge?

105
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,800
You're a liar.

106
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,680
That's a prison code on your neck.

107
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,480
I'm a hacker slash bank robber.

108
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,840
Good. This is a good day
to be a bank robber.

109
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,040
Mutant human. What kind of mutant?

110
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,960
Like he says,
why are you in charge now?

111
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,880
It's my special power. What's yours?

112
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,960
(SIGHS)

113
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:46,160
If I touch living cells,
I can replicate the owner.

114
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,440
-Your face, when we first saw you...
-I touched the worm.

115
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,720
CLARA: You can replicate
their clothes, too?

116
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,600
SAIBRA: I wear a hologram shell.

117
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,320
Human cells.

118
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,920
DNA from a customer, maybe?

119
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,760
A disguise to get us in?

120
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:01,120
We're actually going to do it?
Rob the bank?

121
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,840
DOCTOR:
I don't think we have a choice.

122
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,280
-We've already agreed to.
-(SIGHS)

123
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,800
How long can you maintain
the image for?

124
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,800
For as long as I like.

125
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,880
Question one, robbing banks
is easy if you've got a Tardis.

126
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:51,280
-So why am I not using it?
-Question two, where is the Tardis?

127
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,600
Okay, that probably should
be question one.

128
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,520
-(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
-(ALARM BLARING)

129
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,400
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Banking floor locking down.

130
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,800
They know we're here.

131
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,520
Banking floor locking down.

132
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:45,520
-(WHISPERS) What is that?
-I don't know.

133
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:47,480
Hate not knowing.

134
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:55,560
Excuse me, sir, I regret to say
that your guilt has been detected.

135
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,080
(STAMMERS) Well, that's
totally ridiculous.

136
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,240
Is it, sir?

137
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,160
Well then, we will
certainly double-check.

138
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,640
The Teller will now scan your
thoughts for any criminal intent.

139
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,640
Good luck, sir.

140
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,520
-Interesting.
-PSI: What is?

141
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:13,720
The latest thing in sniffer dogs.
Telepathic.

142
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,440
-(THE TELLER SNARLS)
-It hunts guilt.

143
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:19,520
-What about our guilt?
-Currently being drowned out.

144
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,160
What's he doing?

145
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:26,200
If he has a plan,
trying not to think of it.

146
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,320
Ever tried not thinking
about something?

147
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,320
-CLARA: No.
-You may have to.

148
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,880
(ROARS)

149
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:38,120
Ah, criminal intent detected.
How naughty.

150
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,720
What was your plan?

151
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,520
Counterfeit currency
in your briefcase, perhaps?

152
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,440
No. Not at all. For God's sake...

153
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,040
It really doesn't matter.
We'll establish the details later.

154
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:49,160
The Teller is never wrong
when it comes to guilt.

155
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:52,240
-(GROWLS)
-Your account will now be deleted.

156
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:55,880
And obviously your mind. Supper time.

157
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,880
(THE TELLER SNARLING)

158
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,520
(CUSTOMER GROANING)

159
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,000
(SCREAMS)

160
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,400
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEPING)

161
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:14,000
DOCTOR: It's wiping his mind,
turning his brain into soup.

162
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:17,600
Your next of kin will be
informed and incarcerated

163
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:21,600
as further inducement to
honest financial transactions.

164
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,760
(SCREAMS)

165
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,680
We've got to help him.

166
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,080
He's gone already. It's over.

167
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,440
CLARA: He's in agony. Look at him.

168
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,400
Those aren't tears, Clara. That's soup.

169
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,240
(SCREAMS)

170
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,680
Account closed.

171
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,480
Take him away.

172
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,560
He's ready for his close-up.

173
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,240
(BEEPS)

174
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:56,120
Apologies for the disturbance.
Everyone have a lovely day.

175
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,880
AUTOMATED VOICE: Deposit booth locking.

176
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:10,600
Please exhale. Your valuables will be
transported up from the vault.

177
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,920
-(EXHALES)
-(BEEPS)

178
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,840
Well, if he can break
in here and plant this thing,

179
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:18,280
then why does he need our help?

180
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,240
Depends what the thing is.

181
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,680
Okay, well, I'm no expert
but fuses, a timer,

182
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:25,920
I'm going to stick my neck out
and say bomb.

183
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,920
Bank schematic? Now?

184
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,720
(BEEPS)

185
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,240
(BEEPS)

186
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:47,320
So the man that we captured on
the banking floor wasn't the target?

187
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:50,440
Four bank visitors just entered
the safety deposit box.

188
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,760
The greatest bank in the galaxy.

189
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,680
Our reputation must remain secure.

190
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,680
The Director will blame us.

191
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,520
We'll be fired.

192
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,000
Fired with pain.

193
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:06,360
(RAPID BEEPING)

194
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,720
DOCTOR: The floor below
is all service corridors.

195
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,800
The veins and arteries of the bank.

196
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,120
He wants us to blow through the floor.

197
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,480
-We'll die if we do that.
-Well, not necessarily.

198
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,840
There must be a plan.

199
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:28,120
What if the plan is we're blowing up
the floor for someone else?

200
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,240
What if we're not supposed
to make it out alive?

201
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,920
Ah, don't be so pessimistic.
It'll affect team morale.

202
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,480
SAIBRA: What, and getting us
blown up won't?

203
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,440
-Well, only very, very briefly.
-Er, no, no way.

204
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,560
You can do what you like.
I'm going to take my chances out there.

205
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:42,480
-CLARA: Psi...
-No, this guy, your mate, is a lunatic.

206
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:46,000
What do you want, Psi,
more than anything else?

207
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,480
Whatever it is, it's in this bank.

208
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,280
You agreed to rob the most
impregnable bank in history.

209
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:54,720
You must've had a very good reason.
We all must have.

210
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,440
Picture the thing
you want most in the universe

211
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,160
and decide how badly you want it.

212
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,160
Well?

213
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,200
I still don't understand
why you're in charge.

214
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:14,120
-Basically, it's the eyebrows.
-(BEEPS)

215
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,000
(PULSING HUM)

216
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,040
(PULSING SPEEDS UP)

217
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:37,280
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEPING)

218
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:55,360
Nice! Dimensional shift bomb.

219
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:59,040
Sends the particles
to a different plane.

220
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:04,800
Come on, then, Team Not Dead.

221
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,080
Open up!

222
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,160
Well, so what are we
supposed to do now?

223
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,760
-What's the plan?
-I don't know.

224
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,600
The Architect set all this up.

225
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,160
It should make sense.

226
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:29,920
My personal plan is that a thing
will probably happen quite soon.

227
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,600
So that's it? That's your plan?

228
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:33,280
-Yeah.
-A thing will happen?

229
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,760
A thing. Probably.

230
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,840
Hey, Psi.

231
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,560
Doctor!

232
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,960
DOCTOR: There you go. Thing time.

233
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,880
How does he get the cases here?

234
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,760
By breaking into the bank in advance
of breaking into the bank.

235
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,440
CLARA: Well, how did he do that?

236
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,440
And if he can do that,
why does he need us?

237
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:57,000
-Not our problem.
-Well, what is our pro-pro...

238
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,560
pro-pro-pro...

239
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,480
-You okay?
-Dry glitch. It's fine.

240
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:05,120
Guilt is our problem. Guilt in this bank
is fatal. The Teller can hear it.

241
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:08,160
Ever since that first case was opened,
we've been targets.

242
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,840
The more we know about why we are here,
the louder our guilt screams.

243
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,240
That's why we wiped our memories.
For our own safety.

244
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:18,440
Now, once I open this,
I can't close it again.

245
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:20,520
Would it be safer
if only one of us learned it?

246
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,800
-I'm waiting for you to volunteer.
-PSI: Er, why me?

247
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:27,280
Because you didn't need that memory
worm, did you? You're half-computer.

248
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,680
You can perform a manual delete.

249
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,000
You can clear your thoughts.

250
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,920
PSI: Okay.

251
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,040
(CASE BEEPS)

252
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,800
I don't know what it is.
You may as well have a look.

253
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,480
Well, what are they?

254
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:54,600
-Not a clue.
-SAIBRA: Hmm, interesting.

255
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,320
-What is?
-You're lying.

256
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,680
PSI: Er, why would he be
lying-lying-lying-lying?

257
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:02,560
(GRUNTS) Sorry. Stress.
Drains the batteries.

258
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,520
Interface with this.

259
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,960
Do we have time for this?

260
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:07,640
-Why not? There's no immediate threat.
-(ALARM BLARING)

261
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,800
AUTOMATED VOICE: Warning.
Intruders detected.

262
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,200
I really should stop
saying things like that.

263
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,880
-Intruders detected.
-Clara, step aside.

264
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:18,040
-Saibra, let's go and investigate.
-Intruders detected. Intruders...

265
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,640
(POWERING UP)

266
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:22,160
(PSI GROANS)

267
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:28,720
Storm dust.

268
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,840
You can delete your memories?

269
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,640
Yeah, it's not as fun as it sounds.

270
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,720
I've got a few I wish I could lose.

271
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,280
And I lost a few I wish I hadn't.

272
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,760
No, I was...

273
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,320
I was interrogated in prison.

274
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:43,200
And I guess I panicked.

275
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:46,200
I didn't want to be a risk
to the people close to me, so...

276
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,120
You deleted your friends?

277
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:52,920
My friends, anyone who
ever helped me. My family.

278
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,600
-Your family?
-Of course my family.

279
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,240
How could you do that?

280
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,600
Well, I don't know.

281
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:03,320
(SIGHS) I suppose
I must have loved them.

282
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:16,000
-Aren't you going to ask me?
-Why did you lie?

283
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,120
Those hardware things,
you know what they are.

284
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,560
Exit strategy of sorts.

285
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,960
How did you know I was lying?

286
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:27,000
I've had a lot of faces.
I find them easy to read.

287
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,440
-Quite a gift.
-Gift?

288
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:31,880
-Got us in here.
-Mutant gene.

289
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,640
No one can touch me.

290
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,800
If they do, I transform.

291
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,000
Touch me, Doctor, and you'll
be looking at yourself.

292
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:44,240
-I am alone.
-Why?

293
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:47,800
Could you trust someone who looked
back at you out of your own eyes?

294
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,480
(MOANING NEARBY)

295
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,920
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

296
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:17,600
Oh, my God. Why is he even still alive?

297
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:21,280
I don't know. But someone is watching.

298
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:25,000
Doctor? However this goes,
whatever happens,

299
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:29,040
-don't let me end up like that.
-(ALARM BLARING)

300
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:31,000
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Intruders on the service level

301
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,720
Intruders on the service level

302
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,600
Now this, this is a place to hide.

303
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,520
(SCREWDRIVER WHIRS)

304
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,360
Where are we?

305
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:12,120
(SNARLING)

306
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,920
Nobody move. Nobody say a word!

307
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,600
It's cocooned.

308
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,360
Forced hibernation.

309
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,240
Its power is probably dormant.

310
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:26,520
(MEN RUNNING AND SHOUTING IN HALLWAY)

311
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:30,600
Clara, it's locked on to you.
It may still be asleep. Don't wake it.

312
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:33,520
Okay. How do I not do that?

313
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,440
Keep your mind blank.

314
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,240
Block everything.

315
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,920
Once it locks onto your thoughts,
it won't let go.

316
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:42,800
(SNARLING)

317
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,640
DOCTOR: It's waking up.

318
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:55,640
Keep blocking your thoughts,
Clara. Don't think.

319
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:02,760
-(ROARING)
-This way!

320
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:13,040
-(GASPING)
-DOCTOR: Saibra!

321
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,960
She's still in there.
How do we get her out?

322
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,120
DOCTOR: It's scanning her brain.

323
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,280
-Then what?
-Soup.

324
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,360
-Then help her!
-(THE TELLER ROARING)

325
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,720
(EXCLAIMS)

326
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,520
-Saibra!
-What should I do?

327
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,880
-How can I get away?
-It's rooting through your brain.

328
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,760
It's tasting all the secrets
stashed inside.

329
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:38,680
Any moment now, it will finish its sweep
and start feasting on what's left.

330
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:41,920
And what, then I become one of those
things we saw sitting in a cage?

331
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:43,320
Yes.

332
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,560
Can you not get me out?

333
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:47,720
I'm sorry, I don't know how,
once it's locked onto your thoughts.

334
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,160
(ROARING)

335
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,840
Exit strategy.

336
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:53,800
That means what I think it means, right?

337
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,160
-Atomic shredder.
-Painless?

338
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,920
And instant.

339
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,120
(SNARLING)

340
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,360
When you meet the Architect,
promise me something.

341
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,400
Kill him.

342
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:13,000
I hate him.
But I can't make that promise.

343
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,680
-(THE TELLER SNARLS)
-A good man.

344
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:19,960
I left it late to meet one of those.

345
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:25,520
(GASPS)

346
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,160
(ROARING)

347
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,560
Right. Vault.

348
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,720
That's clear.

349
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,000
What's not clear is what we do now.

350
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,240
Hey... You okay?

351
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:53,640
No, I'm an amnesiac robbing
a bank. Why would I be okay?

352
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:56,040
-Because of Saibra.
-What? Saibra is dead.

353
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:58,200
We're alive. Prioritise if you
want it to stay that way.

354
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:00,920
Oh, is that why you call
yourself the Doctor?

355
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,160
The professional detachment.

356
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:10,800
Listen, when we're done here,
by all means,

357
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:12,520
you go and find yourself
a shoulder to cry on.

358
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:15,880
You'll probably need that.
Till then, what you need is me!

359
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:24,800
Underneath it all,
he isn't really like that.

360
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,720
It's very obvious that you've
been with him for a while.

361
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,400
Why?

362
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,040
Because you are really good
at the excuses.

363
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:35,160
Another gift from the Architect.
Shall we unwrap it?

364
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,920
The unbreakable bank.

365
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,200
We must locate them.

366
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:47,000
And Director Karabraxos must not know.

367
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:51,280
When people get fired here, it's messy.

368
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:58,240
Release the Teller into the tunnels.

369
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:13,520
-(GRUNTS)
-(BEEPING)

370
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:19,520
Right, the system looks like
it's time-delayed.

371
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:21,440
There are 24 lock codes I need to break.

372
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:24,120
Doctor! He's coming, watch out.

373
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,120
-Psi, how long?
-As long as it takes.

374
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:28,080
(THE TELLER SNARLING)

375
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,360
It's locked onto one
of our thought trails.

376
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:33,400
We have to split up,
minimise the brain signals.

377
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,680
What happened to your
professional detachment, Doctor?

378
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:43,200
-No! No!
-In case it finds me.

379
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,840
-It's my choice.
-You don't use that, okay? Promise me.

380
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,400
Time to run.

381
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,960
Separate.

382
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:59,080
(THE TELLER SNARLING IN DISTANCE)

383
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,920
(BEEPING)

384
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:13,440
AUTOMATED VOICE: Vault locks opening.

385
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,360
Vault locks opening.

386
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:20,080
Twenty-four, 23,

387
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:23,200
22,21,

388
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:26,680
20,19, 1817..

389
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:31,680
-(THE TELLER SNARLING)
-(PANTING)

390
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,400
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

391
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,320
DOCTOR: Keep your mind clear, Clara.

392
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:03,600
Keep your mind blank.

393
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,720
(SNARLING)

394
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,520
-(GROWLS)
-(PANTING)

395
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:26,360
-(SNARLS)
-(SCREAMS)

396
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:27,760
Clara!

397
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,960
(PANTING)

398
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:34,560
(BEEPING)

399
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:42,880
PSI: (SHOUTS) Come on!

400
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,440
Come and find me!

401
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:50,240
Every thief and villain
in one big cocktail.

402
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,760
I am so guilty!

403
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:55,360
-(GROANS)
-(THE TELLER SNARLS)

404
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:58,520
Every famous burglar in history
is hiding in this bank

405
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,800
right now in one body!

406
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,760
Come and feast!

407
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,640
(THE TELLER SNARLING)

408
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:10,240
Clara!

409
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:15,120
For what it's worth,
and it might not be worth much,

410
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,120
when your whole life
flashes in front of you,

411
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,480
you see people you love

412
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,720
and people missing you.

413
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,480
And I see no one.

414
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,960
-(SCREAMS)
-(THE TELLER ROARS)

415
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:46,320
AUTOMATED VOICE:
...three, two, one.

416
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:51,880
Failed. Vault unlocking failed.

417
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:53,920
(GRUNTS)

418
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:58,280
CLARA: It's not opening!

419
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:00,040
(PANTING)

420
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,320
Psi.

421
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,360
He died for nothing.

422
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,200
-(SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-Multiple locks.

423
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,000
Last one's still in place.

424
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:23,280
(BEEPING)

425
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,920
(WHIRRING)

426
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:31,360
-(SCREWDRIVER SWITCHES OFF)
-Atomic seal. Unbreakable.

427
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:34,840
Even for me.
The Architect would know that.

428
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,800
He wouldn't bring us
all this way for nothing.

429
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:39,800
-And get two people killed.
-Exactly.

430
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:43,640
-There must be some logic.
-Some logic?

431
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:48,080
Come on, Architect,
what else have you got?

432
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,680
(THUNDER CRASHING)

433
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:54,200
Report, please.
What was the disturbance?

434
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:57,200
Solar storm getting worse.
Interfering with our systems.

435
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:06,560
-(WARNING ALARM)
-Storm.

436
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:11,840
Storm’s tripping the system.

437
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,840
That's what he's got, the storm.

438
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:20,320
How would he know
when a storm would hit?

439
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,360
Of course.

440
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:29,880
Stupid, stupid Doctor.
Of course, of course.

441
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:30,960
Of course what?

442
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,920
Whoever planned all this,
they're in the future.

443
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,480
This isn't just a bank heist.

444
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:40,560
It's a time travel heist.

445
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:46,920
We've been sent back in time to
the exact moment of the storm

446
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:49,360
to be in exactly the right place
when it hits,

447
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:52,920
because that's the only time
that the bank is vulnerable.

448
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:54,640
(LOCK OPENING)

449
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,040
AUTOMATED VOICE: Vault unlocked.

450
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:00,600
The bank is now open.

451
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,480
AUTOMATED VOICE: Vault unlocked.

452
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,880
Come on.

453
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:16,120
Explains why we're not here
in the Tardis.

454
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,280
Sorry, what?

455
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,520
The solar disruption would've
made navigation impossible.

456
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:22,880
The one time the bank is vulnerable
is the one time we can't just land.

457
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:26,480
Doctor, the code. The code
that was in the last case, look.

458
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:30,760
-"Tech.”
-Technology.

459
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:34,160
2-5-1. Find it.

460
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:58,840
CLARA: "Tech."

461
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,640
It's a neophyte circuit.

462
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,120
I've only ever seen one once before.

463
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:15,800
It can reboot any system,
replace any lost data.

464
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:17,680
Psi.

465
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:21,080
That's what he came for. His reward.

466
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,880
So what did Saibra come for?

467
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,760
-Gene suppressant.
-Hmm.

468
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:34,480
-She wanted to be normal.
-Everyone has a weakness.

469
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:36,200
So the big question is this.

470
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:38,960
-What did we come for?
-PV.

471
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:41,800
Private vault. Karabraxos's own fortune?

472
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:48,480
-(SNARLING)
-Intruders are most welcome.

473
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:51,160
They remind us
that the bank is impregnable.

474
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:55,360
It's good for morale to have a few
of you scattered about the place,

475
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:58,240
preferably on view.

476
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:05,760
Are you ready for your close-up?

477
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,920
If you're thinking of ways to escape,

478
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,240
the Teller will know
before you've even made a move.

479
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:14,160
You'll never be bothered
by all that thinking again.

480
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:16,440
-Useful species.
-Last of its kind.

481
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,520
And we've signed an exclusive deal.

482
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:20,880
Must be noisy inside its head.

483
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,760
Painful

484
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:24,960
to listen to so much chatter.

485
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,280
So many secrets.

486
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,080
Must drive it wild.

487
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,000
How can you force it to obey?

488
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:33,800
Oh, everything has a price tag,
I think you'll find.

489
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:35,960
(THUNDER CRASHING)

490
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:38,640
The storm's getting worse.
Customers are leaving.

491
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:41,640
Director Karabraxos will be concerned.

492
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,760
Our jobs will be on the line.

493
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:45,320
You're scared.

494
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:48,240
(CHUCKLES) I'm terrified.

495
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:52,440
I have the disadvantage of
knowing Karabraxos personally.

496
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,680
If you don't like your boss, why stay?

497
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:57,200
My face fits.

498
00:31:57,640 --> 00:32:01,680
Now, if you'll excuse me, I must take
the Teller to its hibernation.

499
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,920
You two, dispose of our guests.

500
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:09,240
(BEEPING)

501
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:17,160
Don't do this.
I'm having a very bad day

502
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:18,480
and I do not want to be pushed around.

503
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:19,600
You're wrong.

504
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:24,280
-DOCTOR: Wrong?
-It's not that bad a day.

505
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,800
And you're being very slow.

506
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,240
Why are you undoing my handcuffs?

507
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:29,800
-(KEYS JINGLING)
-Saibra?

508
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:31,360
Yeah.

509
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:33,720
-PSI: You look like death.
-(LAUGHING)

510
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:36,840
-It was actually a teleporter.
-Oh, my God!

511
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:39,600
Good, eh? You think we're dead
so the Teller thinks we're dead

512
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:41,720
and we played the creature
at its own mind games.

513
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:45,120
No, no, no, no, wait.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

514
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:49,760
Sorry, sorry, you... You...
You're alive?

515
00:32:50,160 --> 00:32:53,160
Yeah. We're alive.
Look at us, we're all alive.

516
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:55,000
No, no, no, no. Not dead.

517
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,000
-Alive.
-There's an escape ship in orbit.

518
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,240
It takes you right there.

519
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:02,240
Oh, and there's this
big blue box. Is that yours?

520
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:05,960
Well, this is good, I suppose.

521
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,480
You'll be able to resume the mission.

522
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:14,200
Gene suppressant,
antidote for your condition.

523
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:23,440
Memory giver. All your yesterdays.

524
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:29,680
There you go. Job done. Paid in full.

525
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,840
-Clever old Architect.
-Very clever.

526
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:33,960
-I still hate him.
-Me, too.

527
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:35,760
-How were you paid?
-I don't know.

528
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:37,600
There's something in the private vault.

529
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,840
-What's that?
-Supply line.

530
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:41,880
It's the only option
down to the private vault.

531
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,640
And there's another one for
water, for basic life support.

532
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:46,360
What, for a private vault?

533
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:50,400
Someone likes to hang out
with their wealth.

534
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,640
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

535
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:36,000
Director Karabraxos.
Excuse us but we've come to rob you.

536
00:34:36,560 --> 00:34:38,880
So if you want to put your hands
above your head or...

537
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:45,240
or?

538
00:34:47,240 --> 00:34:48,920
You didn't bring any weapons.

539
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:52,720
(CHUCKLES) That's a bit of an oversight.

540
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,600
-(BEEP)
-Security, Karabraxos here.

541
00:34:54,680 --> 00:34:56,480
-You're Karabraxos.
-One moment.

542
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:59,480
Director Karabraxos. Is there a problem?

543
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:01,880
Intruders in the private vault.

544
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,040
Send me the Teller.

545
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:05,800
I want to find out how they got in

546
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:08,160
and then I want to wipe their memories.

547
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:09,720
She's a clone.

548
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,680
It's the only way
to control my own security.

549
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,840
I have a clone in every facility.

550
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:16,760
-Get on it right away.
-Yes, of course.

551
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,480
And then, hand in your credentials.

552
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:21,040
You're fired, with immediate effect.

553
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,400
But please, I've been in your service...

554
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:25,760
Ever since the last one let me down
and I was forced to kill it.

555
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,360
I can't quite believe that you're
putting me through this again.

556
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,000
-(BEEPS)
-My clone.

557
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:31,800
And yet, she doesn't even protest.

558
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,480
Pale imitation, really.

559
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,200
(LAUGHS) I should sue.

560
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:38,000
-You're killing her? You just said...
-Fired?

561
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:41,920
I put all of the used clones
into the incinerator.

562
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:44,880
Can't have too many of mo/
scattered around.

563
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,280
Sorry, you don't get on
with your own clone?

564
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:49,520
She hates her own clones.

565
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:52,400
She burns her own clones.

566
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:55,800
Frankly, you're a career break
for the right therapist.

567
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:02,080
Shut up.

568
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:04,400
Everybody, just... Just shut up.

569
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:06,560
And what is this display?
Now, as amusing as you are...

570
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:11,000
Shut up. Just shut up. Shut up.
Shut up. Shuttity up-up-up!

571
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:16,880
What... What did you say?

572
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:20,440
What did... What did you say?

573
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:23,000
What did you say about your own eyes?

574
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:25,080
De-shut up. Say it again.

575
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:28,280
How can you trust someone if they look
back at you out of your own eyes?

576
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:31,120
I know one thing about the Architect.

577
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,560
What is it that I know
about the Architect?

578
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:35,520
I know one thing, something that
I have known from the very start.

579
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:37,080
CLARA: What?

580
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:38,520
I hate him!

581
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:42,920
He's overbearing, he's manipulative,

582
00:36:43,520 --> 00:36:47,680
he likes to think that
he's very clever. I hate him!

583
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:50,080
-Clara, don't you see?
-(GONGING)

584
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:53,280
I hate the Architect.

585
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,880
What in the name of sanity
is going on in this room now?

586
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,400
We're getting sanity judgement
from the self-burner.

587
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:01,240
Do you mind if I borrow
a little bit of paper?

588
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:04,760
And what are you doing now?

589
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:06,040
I'm giving you

590
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,400
my telephone number.

591
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:10,560
Why?

592
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:15,560
Well, I thought you might
like to call me someday.

593
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:19,560
Sorry, I thought we were getting
along famously.

594
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:21,920
Am I like, misreading
the signals or something?

595
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,320
(THUNDER CRASHING)

596
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,360
Oh, boy, that was a big one, wasn't it?

597
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:28,240
I think that your bank is about
to close for good, Karabraxos.

598
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:31,160
If I was you, I'd get going.
Don't mind us.

599
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:33,160
We'll just stay here and burn.

600
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:36,840
(ALARM BLARING)

601
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:41,120
(ALL SCREAMING)

602
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,360
DOCTOR: Hard to know what to take.

603
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:45,640
The greatest treasures in the
universe and just one suitcase.

604
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:48,440
(RUMBLING)

605
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:52,400
Doctor, what's the plan?
Is there a plan?

606
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,320
Well, we can use the shredders
and get us back to the ship.

607
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:55,640
They're not shredders,
they're teleporters.

608
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,080
That's not the most interesting
thing about them.

609
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:58,800
-So what is?
-There were six of them.

610
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,000
Hey.

611
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:05,360
-Give me a call sometime.
-AUTOMATED VOICE: Doors opening.

612
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:06,720
You'll be dead.

613
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,640
Yeah, you'll be old.
We'll get on famously.

614
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:13,040
You'll be old and full of regret
for the things that you can't change.

615
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:18,600
AUTOMATED VOICE: Doors closing.

616
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:25,120
Doctor, what the hell is going on?

617
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:28,400
-Are you remembering?
-No, not a thing.

618
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:30,840
-But I'm understanding.
-What?

619
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:32,280
What is it? What are you understanding?

620
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:35,880
I'm not sure yet. I need my memory back

621
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:38,760
and I think that
there's only one way to do that.

622
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,640
-Which would be?
-Soup.

623
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,440
-Soup...
-(LIFT BELL DINGS)

624
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:45,760
(SNARLING)

625
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:50,320
Hello, big man.

626
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,640
-Biggies.
-CLARA: Doctor!

627
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:57,680
No! No! Let it take me.

628
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:00,240
Let it read me!

629
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:02,160
-It's the only way.
-It will kill you.

630
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,120
What have I told you about pessimism?

631
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:07,240
That's it. That's it.

632
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:09,720
There are so many memories in here.

633
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:12,960
Feast on them.

634
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:14,680
Tuck in.

635
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,120
Big scarf.

636
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:18,600
Bow tie, bit embarrassing.

637
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:20,920
What do you think of the new look?

638
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:23,080
I was hoping for minimalism

639
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:25,000
but I think I came out with magician.

640
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:30,040
But the last few days,
there's been a block.

641
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:34,360
Can you see the block?

642
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,640
Tell me why I'm here!

643
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,600
-Show me why I'm here.
-(SNARLING)

644
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,680
Show me!

645
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:46,120
-(PHONE RINGING)
-It's just a phone, Clara.

646
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:48,000
Nothing happens
when you answer the phone.

647
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:50,560
-Doctor.
-Hello?

648
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:55,040
You gave me this number.
My name is Madame Karabraxos.

649
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,760
-(STEADY BEEPING)
-I was once

650
00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:01,400
the wealthiest person in the universe.

651
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:03,000
I need your assistance.

652
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,160
I am dying.

653
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,640
With many, many regrets.

654
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,480
But one, perhaps,

655
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:14,240
you may be able to help me with.

656
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,400
There's a little detour. It's a job.

657
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:19,600
I've got to do it for someone. Come on.

658
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:21,920
-We need to rob a bank.
-What?

659
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,960
Clara, I need worms.

660
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:26,280
(TARDIS WHIRRING)

661
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:34,040
The bank of Karabraxos
has never been breached.

662
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:44,040
-Architect.
-DISTORTED VOICE: Architect.

663
00:40:44,720 --> 00:40:46,680
-Architect.
-(PITCH CHANGING) Architect.

664
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:48,400
-Architect.
-(DEEPER, DISTORTED) Architect.

665
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:49,960
Architect.

666
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:51,960
(SQUEAKING)

667
00:40:56,960 --> 00:41:00,880
DOCTOR: You will rob
the bank of Karabraxos.

668
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:04,600
DOCTOR: Did you see?

669
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:08,200
Why we came!

670
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,120
Why we're here!

671
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,520
We had to delete our own memories.

672
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:14,600
Otherwise, you'd have known
and then she'd have known

673
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:15,920
because you were mentally linked.

674
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:19,120
But she's gone now. They've all gone.

675
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,360
They have no power over you now.

676
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,920
You can do exactly
what you want to do now.

677
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,560
Exactly what you've
always wanted to do.

678
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:27,960
(SNARLS)

679
00:41:28,040 --> 00:41:29,560
(LOCK CLICKING)

680
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:37,520
It knows the combination.

681
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,400
Of course it does.
It was linked to Karabraxos.

682
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:42,320
What exactly are we doing here?
That thing killed people.

683
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,120
Well, so might you do
to protect everything you loved.

684
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:47,400
(DOOR OPENING)

685
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:49,720
(MOANING)

686
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:54,320
DOCTOR: There she is.

687
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:58,000
Not the last of its species.
The last two.

688
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:01,800
(MOANING)

689
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:06,120
It's okay.

690
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,960
It's okay. It's all right.

691
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:12,360
Exit strategy. We've got six shredders.

692
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,000
Exactly.

693
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:16,360
This wasn't a bank heist.

694
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:18,040
It never was.

695
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:21,920
It was a rescue mission
for a whole species.

696
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,880
Flesh and blood. The last currency.

697
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:28,040
-(RUMBLING)
-Time to go home.

698
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:29,880
What do you think of that, big man?

699
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:32,480
(ROARING)

700
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:40,120
So much mental traffic in the universe.

701
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:43,560
Solitude is the only peace.

702
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:47,520
(BOTH MOANING)

703
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:59,680
DOCTOR: Cesare Borgia,
mucho scary hombre, says to me,

704
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:01,320
"What do you think of our
leaning tower of Pisa?"

705
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,280
I say, "It looks okay to me."

706
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:04,680
(ALL LAUGHING)

707
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:12,480
If you ever need help
with another bank heist...

708
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:20,320
Yeah, it's not really his area.

709
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:32,520
See? I don't have your face now.

710
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:35,160
-Yeah, I kind of miss that.
-Oh, shut up.

711
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:46,520
7:12 local time, as promised.
Go and enjoy yourself.

712
00:43:46,600 --> 00:43:47,760
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

713
00:43:47,840 --> 00:43:49,640
This is a date. You know,

714
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:52,240
I've just realised I'm going out
for another meal now.

715
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:56,480
Don't worry, calories consumed
on the Tardis have no lasting effect.

716
00:43:56,600 --> 00:43:57,960
Wha... Are you kidding?

717
00:43:58,040 --> 00:44:00,480
Of course I'm kidding. It's a time
machine, not a miracle worker.

718
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:02,680
-Bye-bye.
-See ya! Don't rob any banks!

719
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,480
Don't rob any banks what?

720
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:07,000
Without me.

721
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:08,800
Course not, boss.

722
00:44:14,800 --> 00:44:17,080
Robbing a bank. Robbing a whole bank.

723
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,600
Beat that for a date.

724
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:27,960
-You okay?
-Yeah, of course I'm okay.

725
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:29,280
Why wouldn't I be okay?

726
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:31,440
I don't know. Every time I see you
it's like you're...

727
00:44:31,520 --> 00:44:34,080
-What?
-In a rush. In a state.

728
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:35,320
How's you?

729
00:44:35,400 --> 00:44:37,400
-Sorry I'm late.
-Who are you having dinner with?

730
00:44:37,480 --> 00:44:38,920
(PANTING) I can't keep doing this.

731
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:40,720
I can't do it.

732
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,840
The next few days are all about you.

733
00:44:43,560 --> 00:44:44,880
I promise.

734
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:46,800
I'm the new caretaker.

735
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:49,200
-John Smith.
-Welcome to Coal Hill, Mr Smith.

736
00:44:49,280 --> 00:44:50,320
DOCTOR: Thanks.

737
00:44:50,400 --> 00:44:53,680
ROBOTIC VOICE:
Problem. Solution: destroy.

